  <RulesElement name="Acid Blood Brew (level 5)" type="Magic Item" internal-id="ID_TIV_MAGIC_ITEM_10040_26_01" source="Buck-A-Batch Magic Potions (Book 2)" revision-date="12/14/2010 10:35 AM">
    <Flavor> Possibly it's just Coppermine Ale with flicks of black dragon scale floating in it. Possibly it's something more... </Flavor>
    <specific name="Level"> 5 </specific>
    <specific name="Gold"> 50 </specific>
    <specific name="Magic Item Type"> Potion </specific>
    <specific name="Tier"/>
    <specific name="_Item_Set_ID"/>
    <specific name="Armor"/>
    <specific name="Weapon"/>
    <specific name="Item Slot"/>
    <specific name="Requirement"/>
    <specific name="Critical"/>
    <specific name="Special"> Many brews are dwarven in origin and may have an alcoholic base. Make a saving throw when consuming this potion. If you fail you suffer a penalty of 1 to your attack rolls for the duration of the potion's effect. </specific>
    <specific name="Power"> Power (Consumable * Acid): Minor Action. Use this power after you drink the potion. If an attack causes you to become bloodied during this encounter you immediatily deal 2d4 acid damage with ongoing 5 acid damage to creatures in squares adjacent to yours (save ends). If a creature's melee attack caused you to become bloodied that creature suffers a penalty of 1 to its attack rolls and a penalty of 1 to its AC until the end of the encounter. The potion's effects wear off at the end of the encounter. </specific>
    <specific name="_Rarity"> Common </specific>
    <specific name="Property"/>
  </RulesElement>
